#: ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:17(title) 
msgid "Databases"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:18(para) 
msgid "Ubuntu provides two popular database servers. They are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:26(application) ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:140(title) 
msgid "PostgreSQL"
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:29(para) 
msgid "They are available in the main repository. This section explains how to install and configure these database servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../generic/serverguide/C/databases.xml:36(para) 
msgid "MySQL is a fast, multi-threaded, multi-user, and robust SQL database server. It is intended for mission-critical, heavy-load production systems as well as for embedding into mass-deployed software."
